div.p:
I own the Word Zeal is frequently in Scripture taken in a bad sence; Emulations [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] are by St. Paul reckon'd among the works of the Flesh, Gal. 5.20. And St. James cautions us against [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] Bitter Envying, or Zeal. Ja. 3.14. And indeed it is the Object of our Zeal together with its manner of acting, that renders it either Vertuous or Unlawful, a Duty or a Sin.
